'''Stanley E. Clarke III''' is a retired [[United States Air Force]] [[Lieutenant general (United States)|lieutenant general]] and former Director of the [[Air National Guard]]. In that position, he was the highest-ranking member of the [[Air National Guard]] and reported directly to the Chief of the [[National Guard Bureau]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ang.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123341445 | title = Air Force Lt. Gen. Stanley E. Clarke assumes helm as Air Guard director | author = Jon Soucy | publisher = United States Air Force |date= 23 Mar 2013 | accessdate= 25 Oct 2013}}</ref>
==Biography== Clarke was commissioned as a Second Lieutenant in the [[United States Air Force]] following his graduation from the [[University of Georgia]] in with a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree in 1981. He is a Command Pilot and has flown over 4,000 hours (including over 100 combat hours) in the [[Fairchild Republic A-10 Thunderbolt II|A-10 Thunderbolt]], [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16 Fighting Falcon]], and [[Fairchild C-26 Metroliner|C-26 Metroliner]]. He has served in a number of leadership positions including Commander of the [[160th Fighter Squadron]], Commander of the [[187th Fighter Wing]], Deputy Director of the [[Air National Guard]], Defense Attache in [[Turkey]], Assistant Adjutant General of the [[Alabama National Guard]], and Commander of the [[First Air Force]]. In 2007, he completed a [[Master of Arts]] degree in [[military studies]] at the [[American Military University]].<ref name=afbio>{{cite web | url=http://www.af.mil/AboutUs/Biographies/Display/tabid/225/Article/108030/lieutenant-general-stanley-e-clarke-iii.aspx | title = Lieutenant General Stanley E Clarke III | publisher = United States Air Force |date= Oct 2013 | accessdate= 25 Oct 2013}}</ref>
In May 2013, he was promoted to Lieutenant General and became the Director of the [[Air National Guard]].<ref name=afbio/> He was relieved of this assignment on 18 December 2015<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.airforcetimes.com/story/military/guard-reserve/2016/01/04/-10-flights-fond-memory-retiring-air-national-guard-director/78274178/|title=A-10 flights are fond memory for retiring Air National Guard director|author=Phillip Swarts|date=4 January 2016|website=AirForceTimes|accessdate=1 April 2016}}</ref> and retired from the U.S. Air Force on 1 March 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.af.mil/AboutUs/Biographies/Display/tabid/225/Article/108030/lieutenant-general-stanley-e-clarke-iii.aspx | title = Lieutenant General Stanley E. Clarke III | publisher = U.S. Air Force| accessdate=1 April 2016}}</ref>
